OL,3,CMSPs back Assisted Dying Bill at stage
OL,4,Cone
OL,6,FA number of high profile politicians
OL,7,Fin Scotland voted against the bill,
OL,8,Fincluding the First Minister John
OL,9,FSwinney, deputy first minister Kate
OL,10,FForbes and the former first ministers
OL,11,FNicola Sturgeon and Humza Yousaf.
OL,13,FScottish Labour MSP Pam Duncan-Glancy
OL,14,Fsaid: "As the Scottish parliament's
OL,15,Ffirst permanent wheelchair user, i am
OL,16,Fasking colleagues today to vote
OL,17,Fagainst the bill and to stand up for
OL,18,Fdisabled people and others who, like
OL,19,Fme, are deeply worried about the
OL,20,Fconsequences of legalising assisted
OL,21,Fsuicide.
OL,26,@vD@GOU
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G4/14
