OL,4,Cone
OL,6,FHe has engaged positively with those
OL,7,Fhe is trying to persuade and those who
OL,8,Fhe cannot.
OL,10,FThat is vital when it comes to
OL,11,Fconsidering counter arguments like
OL,12,Fthose put forward by Labour MSP Pam
OL,13,FDuncan Glancy, the first wheelchair-
OL,14,Fbound MSP, who has powerfully
OL,15,Farticulated her worries that a change
OL,16,Fto the law would legitimise the view
OL,17,Fthat a life of dependence and often
OL,18,Fpain "is not worth living".
